author: Matthew Cahill
title: Golf roundup | Kellam places two in top 10 at state tourney
text:
Group 6A state championships Kellam's Leonard Park fired a 1-under 71 in the final round to capture second place at Magnolia Green Golf Course in Moseley on Tuesday.
Kellam finished third out of four teams, 27 strokes behind champion Chantilly. South County's David Ross also shot a 71 to finished two strokes ahead of Park for the individual title.
Kellam's Cam Barackman finished tied for eighth, shooting a final-round 72. Landstown's Brendan Kelly (t-11th), First Colonial's Teddy Hoffmann (t-11th) and Landstown's Raphael Olfato (t-14th) finished in the top 15.
____
Group 5A state championships
Hickory's Patrick Gareiss bested his first round by a stroke, shooting a 4-over 76 to finished tied for eighth at Magnolia Green Golf Course in Moseley.
Gareiss was South Hampton Roads' top contender in the event. Deep Run won the team competition, 14 shots better than second-place Thomas Jefferson.
Jefferson's Nathan Chuwait carded a second straight 2-under 70 to capture medalist honors. Stafford's Jacoby Smith placed second, eight shots behind.
Deep Run's Alex Taylor was third with a two-day total of 149.
The state championship is Deep Run's second 5A title in three years. Four Wildcats shot under 79 on the tournament's final day.
____
Group 4A state championships
Great Bridge's Carter Old and EJ Whiten helped the Wildcats finish third in the team competition at Glenrochie Golf Course in Abingdon.
Loudoun Valley won the title by one stroke over E.C. Glass. Monacan finished fourth.
Loudoun Valley's Brandon Weaver shot a final-round 74 to win the individual competition, two strokes ahead of Derrick Chocklett (William Byrd).
Old shot matching 81s to finished tied for 13th, while Whiten shot a pair of 82s to wind up tied for 20th.
